DAMATURU – Preparatory to the distribution of over 3,000 houses recently completed by the Governor of Yobe State, Mai Mala Buni, the Yobe State Housing and Property Development Corporation have agreed to partner with Yobe Microfinance Bank to facilitate payments on behalf of Yobe State Government. The two Managing Directors held a joint meeting at the office of the Managing Director for Yobe State Housing and Property Development Corporation QS Muhammad Hadi. The Managing Director, Yobe Microfinance Bank Dr Sheriff Muhammad Ibrahim has promised to develop a product that will ensure transparency in the modes of collection and ensure quarterly remittances to the accounts of the Yobe State Revenue Board. “Yobe State Housing and Property Development Corporation has been the leading institution with over two decades of existing relationship Yobe Microfinance Bank, thus, this effort is a continuation of an already existing relationship” he says. Give Us Access To Diaspora Remittances, ABCON Tells CBN Equities Market Closes 2021 Positive At 6.07% On his part, the Managing Director, Yobe State Housing and Property Development Corporation insisted that beneficiaries will be provided with the introductory letters to present to the Bank for account opening.